latestIgtvVideos.title: A curling hair tutorial !  Getting Help from a Friend!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I’ve always longed for curly, wavy hair and have tried so many curling irons, with little success!  When my Insta-buddy @alice_inthe_looking_glass spotted yet another failed attempt on my stories she came to my rescue and offered to teach me how to use a curling iron!. 
At the same time, the brilliant @t3micro hair tool specialists sent me their latest curling wand to try.  So we met at the @themayfairtownhouse Hotel for a special one-to-one session which was brilliant and we created this IGTV to share Alice's method and top tips! 
I learnt lots!  Curling hair hacks include – sectioning hair into three, using a scrunchy not a hair clip -  Curl hair away from the face and make sure the clippy bit of the iron is facing forward!  Back home and I'm getting better.  Definitely less tantrums!! 
We hope you enjoy and find it useful.  We would love to hear any of your top hair curling tips, especially any great hair products … and like, save and share if you found it useful. 
Thank you @alice_inthe_looking_glass , @t3micro (PR Product) and @themayfairtownhouse for the gorgeous room and hospitality

latestPosts.caption:
AS SEEN IN @whowhatwear.uk 

You can slay at any age guys!  At the weekend guess who was featured in @whowhatwear.uk ? Yes ME 🙌

Super proud and it wasn’t a tiddly feature … no, it was a massive piece!  Proving that style has no expiration date ! After decades of hiding my real age, I’m feeling fabulous at 59 and honoured to be interviewed by my favourite online magazine and daily newsletter. 
Swipe to see my 6 ageless trends to refresh your wardrobe and linked on stories to get some great shopping get-the-look inspiration from Who What Wear. 
 
AND big hello to any new followers on here.  Thanks so much for joining me here.  I’m a London based fashion PR, and have run my own business for a couple of decades.  I’m turning 60 in the summer, and after decades of lying about my age I eventually came out last autumn … I know ridiculous,
but thanks to social media and all your wonderful women out there, I’ve gained the confidence to embrace my age and be proud of it.  One of my big fears is getting cancelled professionally with so much #ageism in the work place but I figured  we need to trail blaze for the generations to come – so I’m hoping that won’t happen to me.  As well as style, beauty and wellness tips, I’ll be embracing every milestone and wrinkle as I embark on my last year in my 50s. 
 
Lots of love, Marie Louise xx
